author: @uvideo100
text: Wow, fantastic story. Hat's off to your teacher, and all committed teachers. He was being humble in stating that he learnt something from 5th standard students. Look at the big picture. He gives 15 minutes of stage time to every student. Helps remove stage fright later in life. Helps them build their presentation skills. More important, helps them to find their passion at that age. Perfectly okay if the passion changes later on in life. And, as you indicated, everything cannot be taught in school. Perfectly fine if your passion is not what is in 5th standard syllabus. And he demonstrated that he is a lifelong learner, inspiring the students to be the same, by acknowledging that he learnt something today from the students. Thank you for sharing. Krish.
